  "title": "M&E Coordinator/Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>Review project specifications and technical clarifications.</p>\n<p>Supervise the M&amp;E works and coordinate with client, consultants and sub-contractors.</p>\n<p>Understand contract requirements and M&amp;E specifications in order to monitor progress, quality of workmanship and compliance with project requirements/construction schedule.</p>\n<p>Coordinate with in-house architectural &amp; structural team to minimize discrepancies.</p>\n<p>Check and prepare material sample with shop drawing submission.</p>\n<p>Prepare M&amp;E coordination drawings and liaise with Architectural Coordinators and Design Engineers for drawing issuance.</p>\n<p>Assess, prepare and submit progress claims for project consultants &amp; subcontractors.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>Candidate must possess at least Bachelor's Degree/Post Graduate Diploma/Professional Degree, Master's Degree in Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), Engineering (Mechanical) or equivalent.</p>\n<p>At least 5 Year(s) of working experience in main-con, preferably in HDB project.</p>",
